cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a novel hardware system that implements migratory memory-side processing and evaluates irregular algorithms such as SpMV, BFS, and graph alignment. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.AR (Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.PF (Performance), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Among these, cs.AR and cs.DC are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the hardware and distributed nature of the Emu Chick system. cs.DS and cs.PF are also likely categories as they deal with algorithmic performance and optimization. cs.PL is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages per se, but rather on programming strategies for irregular algorithms on a specific hardware system.
